				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13445472#post-4737108</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13445472/scp-5976#post-4737108</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 03 Aug 2020 05:00:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Hugh Manatee</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3557786</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I think you should move this sentence:</p> <blockquote> <p>Approximately 97.3% of subjects die of either blunt force trauma or immolation within an hour of SCP-5976's activation.</p> </blockquote> <p>So that it follows this paragraph:</p> <blockquote> <p>If the subject attempts to hide by under their body covering, it will start to rapidly increase in weight and retaining temperature3. If the subject attempts to find SCP-5976-1 and prevents it from playing the refrain, SCP-5976-2 will grab the subject and vocalize the phrase, &quot;No, no.&quot; SCP-5976-2 will demanifest if the subject stops the refrain.</p> </blockquote> <p>For greater effect.</p> <p>This sentence here could benefit from deleting the words &quot;by&quot; and &quot;retaining&quot;:</p> <blockquote> <p>If the subject attempts to hide by under their body covering, it will start to rapidly increase in weight and retaining temperature.</p> </blockquote> <p>Other than that, great article! I would love to see some tests where they attempt to remove every possible source of music from the bedroom, and the anomaly has to get creative.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
